Nappanee Apple Festival was sharing a COVID-19 Update.
July 14 at 1:36 PM ¬∑

It is with a heavy heart that the Nappanee Apple Festival Core Committee announces that the 2020 festival will be canceled due to health concerns surrounding the COVID-19 pandemic.

The Nappanee Apple Festival Core Committee, in partnership with the City of Nappanee, feels this decision is in the best interest of our sponsorship partners, vendors, volunteers, visitors‚Äô health and safety. After months of brainstorming, we concluded that the safest option was to cancel this year‚Äôs festival. The well being and safety of our community is the Apple Festival Committee‚Äôs top priority.

We are genuinely humbled by the overwhelming support from the community over the years, and we are confident that the 2021 Nappanee Apple Festival will be better than ever. We want to thank everyone for making this event such a special piece of Nappanee‚Äôs history. Stay safe and we will see you in September of 2021!

Sincerely,
The Nappanee Apple Festival Core Committee

On June 29th, the Elkhart County Health Department issued a Face Covering Mandate effective on June 30th, 2020.

The mandate requires that a resident wear a face mask at all indoor areas open to the public, outdoor areas where a distance of 6 feet cannot be maintained from individual outside one's household, and private indoor/outdoor areas where a distance of 6 feet cannot be maintained from individuals outside one's household.

GRASS CLIPPINGS:

It's that time of year again! If your grass clippings go into the street the clippings can clog the street drains and potentially cause the sewer lines to become backed up. Please be mindful when mowing your yard that you try to keep grass out of the streets.

If you can, bag your grass, or put it in your trash container or buy bag tags at Martin's.

PLAN COMMISSION:
The Nappanee Plan Commission will meet on Thursday, March 26, at 7 PM. They will be holding a public hearing on the replat of Amish Acres. Due to the coronavirus and the Indiana Governor‚Äôs Executive Orders 20-08 and 20-09 issued March 23rd, this meeting will be a virtual meeting.

Here are ways you can offer public comment for this public hearing. The meeting will be available using the Zoom app. You can participate virtually by joining the meeting by video (Meeting ID: 594 503 025) or calling 312-626-6799 and entering the meeting ID (594 503 025), followed by #. You may also submit comments ahead of the meeting via email by sending them to dlehman@nappanee.org prior to 7 PM, March 26th. If you would like to submit comments in writing, please call City Hall at 574-773-2112 and arrange a time to drop off your comments prior to 5 PM on March 26th. For any questions, or to see the replat, please call Don Lehman at 574-773-2112.

January 17 at 1:11 AM ¬∑

Hello everyone! ‚ú®‚ú®‚ú® The Nappanee Arts council is excited to announce TWO projects for the 2020 year! We‚Äôre very excited to bring new creative opportunities to help enrich our community, and we‚Äôve been excited to share them with you!

Le Tour de Nappanee and Woodland Creatures! With the participation and support of our community, The Nappanee Arts Council will be adding "The Dog Pound" and "Woodland Creatures" to The Art Path this spring and replacing The Junkyard Dogs downtown with "Le Tour de Nappanee."

The first project is Tour de Nappanee, a bicycle project that celebrates individuality, tourism, community, and creativity. It will replace Be on the lookout for more information and updates about this project! We are accepting applicants and this project is open to the public!
